			>
			<DIV>did you really think that SOE is listening now? that some how&nbsp;Mr. Smelly see's his bottom line dropping that the dev's would suddenly change their die cast molds of what they expect and require of clerics?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Head on over to Lucy:&nbsp; <A href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/" target=_blank>http://lucy.allakhazam.com/</A></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>In spell search, type in "Hand of Conviction"&nbsp; (level 70)</DIV>
<DIV>now search for "Conscience" &nbsp;(level 70)</DIV>
<DIV>How about the single cast "Conviction" (level 67)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>What do ya see?&nbsp; Peridots?&nbsp; Thats right baby, these suckers are just like Virtue and Hand of Virtue and our symbol, 2 peri's for groups, 1 peri's for singles.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>We've made it clear to sony that most clerics hate them.&nbsp; That its patently unfair that other classes (druids) can cast really great buffs such as BO9 without any reagents.&nbsp; They cause controversy in pickup groups (adds yet another reason to avoid them) and for a mid level cleric (44-55) they are excessivly costly for anyone but die hard LDON junkies.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Sony isnt going to change a thing, they hate our epic, they hate our Complete Heal spell, wish they could undo them.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Cancel your omens order in protest!&nbsp; Stop being a puppy slave!</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
