		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Kytherea wrote:<BR>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>"Ok, I went and spoke directly to Rytan about these spells you are seeing on Lucy for 66-70.&nbsp; He said the spells you see are just the start....they want to get the obvious upgrade spells done and out of the way, but the spells you see are definitely not&nbsp;finished yet. Eventually they will start working on some new spells as well as upgrades to the old ones."</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV></DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV>The point in voicing these concerns is that what are "obvious upgrade spells" to Rytan are not so obvious to the rest of us.&nbsp; We've officially asked that peridot costs be removed from our symbol and aegolism spell lines, yet they're present in the spell data shown on Lucy for these "obvious" upgrade spells.&nbsp; Has a decision been made to deny our request to have our second rate spell penalty removed?&nbsp; Are the mana costs on those spells final?&nbsp; Are the devs going to make further adjustments to the HP/AC/mana/reagent costs for the "obvious upgrade spells" or will they be focused on adding new spells instead?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Please print out Hurk's post if you need to, take it to Rytan and show him <STRONG>why</STRONG> the cleric community is dissatisfied with the cookie cutter approach to spell upgrades.&nbsp; And before you do, please be aware that IMO requiring members of&nbsp;any class to get AAs and focus effect items to bring mana costs back in line with the sub-50 game is inappropriate.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>	
