<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
valeriane_inno wrote:<BR>
<P>Second whats the problem on Pdots ? A stack goes for 220pp, look at Necro ( EE cost 400 + ) , At Wizards or some other classes. I have no single problem with buying Gems for spells, since if you need money go PoH or some other money zone. </P>
<DIV></DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>The difference between peridots and EEs is that dots are required to play and EEs are not.&nbsp; I've gone through untold stacks of dots over the years with my cleric.&nbsp; My necro, created on the same day my cleric was and also played (not PLed) to 65 by me personally, has never once used an EE.&nbsp; They're both on the same account, so no, I can't use my cleric to rez my necro when she dies.</P>
<P>While I grant you that my necro may be at one end of the spectrum in terms of EE usage, I use this example to illustrate my point.&nbsp; Necros don't <STRONG>have</STRONG> to use EEs to play EverQuest.&nbsp; The same can't be said of a cleric and peridots.&nbsp; Dot costs really hurt from mid-40s to mid-50s.&nbsp; Now they're just an annoyance.&nbsp; Like a small insect that just won't leave you alone.</P>
