<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&message.id=1360#M1360">15</a> of 113
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1306 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Mhyrrin wrote:<BR>At least it's still a peridot and not another higher costing gem.&nbsp; With the amount of hp our buffs give, we have to pay some price.
<DIV></DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>At the time that spells were invented, almost every caster class was given a high end "situational" use spell. These spells... Avatar for shaman, Symbol for clerics, Runes for wizards, Necros, and Enchanters. Pets and other spells for Mages, etc. All had components as part of the cost.&nbsp; This was to balance the fact that these spells made you beyond normal in your power. They were never intended for constant use. (testament to this is that clerics outside of raids almost never used symbols, and vox and nag were once a week, so the other 5 days were exping or raids in teh planes after they were released)</P>
<P>Fast forward to now. For some qirk of fate, enchanters have a free self rune. Wizards and Necromancers have a free self rune. Mages can eliminate the need but to carry a single malachite, and have pets that in fact have no component. Of those spells left punished are coth for mages(pearl to cast), necromancer high end pets (dot to cast) necromancer res (essence emerald), runes castable on others for chanters (dot to cast), Divine intervention for clerics(2 emeralds), and Symbol for clerics(dot to cast).&nbsp; There are for sure some i have missed, and druids for instance must still carry a fire beetle eye, though they do have other spells with similer effects to those that require it. </P>
<P>So, on a raid, how often do necros res? use pets?&nbsp; how often do chanters rune someone? how often do mages coth?&nbsp;&nbsp; sometimes for sure.&nbsp; in certian cases mages must coth a raid several times, VT for instance. But what about clerics?&nbsp; how often do you DI the main tank... then yourself... and the chanters... oh and the off tanks.&nbsp; How often do you symbol someone?&nbsp; virtue them? the answer would be "every time someone dies, comes to teh raid, and even sometimes at the end so they can go solo"</P>
<P>Yes, we face a high cost vs most classes. not just dots, but emeralds as well.&nbsp; some of that I really dont mind. the raid can pay for the emeralds for example. its the cost of doing business (just as some raids always have the main tank drink a fire shield, or have members use shrink potions) But the day to day cost of dots for buffing... mind you buffs your expected to have at that, well, no other class still has that penalty. topping that with Virtue actually being less useful than symbol + nines, and having to cast it twice as often is insult upon injury.</P>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=411608">Hurk</a><br>~~~~~<br>"Character is always lost when a high ideal is sacrificed on the altar of conformity and popularity." - Anon<br><br>"You can tell the character of someone by how they treat those that can do nothing for them." -Hendrix
							</div>
								
