		" 
			>
			<P>Depending on the raid, necros summon and spend an infinite amount of money for coffins.&nbsp; Xegony anyone?&nbsp; The guild pays the cost of the coffins.</P>
<P>Most every raid mages coh, the guild pays the cost of the COH.</P>
<P>I symbol every single raid, I get reimbursed for the cost of the peridot.&nbsp; If I DI, I get a stack of gems from the raid leader before the raid begins.&nbsp; If they don't have gems on them, I get cash drops to compensate.&nbsp; Right now my out of pocket cost are nil.</P>
<P>Clerics cast the highest hp buffs in game, we are going to have to pay the price for that.&nbsp; If you are in a group and your group wants a buff that will cost you 2 peridots to cast, then make sure you get a cash drop to compensate for your expenditure.&nbsp; In experience groups I have NEVER had to ask, they have always made sure I got the first diamond that dropped.&nbsp; If you have to ask and are turned down, leave the group they are jerks.</P>
<P>I would love if the gem requirement were removed from our spells, especially DI.&nbsp; But seeing how many times DI has saved the main tank in a raid and saved the raid in general I don't see it being removed.&nbsp; You have to pay some price for that kind of power.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
