<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
-Evil-Robot-Arvor wrote:<BR><BR>
<DIV>Do you have an estimated date for when we can check to see if SOE is actually doing anything regarding cleric concerns?<BR>
<HR>
</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>I believe that would be August 31, 2004, the date OoW goes live.&nbsp; That's the day my accounts will be canceled if they're still jerking us around, at any rate.&nbsp; They asked for feedback, we gave them a ton of it.&nbsp; The amount of time they pushed back the OoW release so they could address our concerns is rapidly slipping away.&nbsp; Grumbuk is knocking himself out working on DX9 issues, and we appreciate that and his level of communication with the player base&nbsp;more than they can possibly know.</P>
<P>So where's the rest of the SOE staff?&nbsp; First we got put off because of E3.&nbsp; Then they collected an enormous amount of feedback from the masses.&nbsp; That promptly got put on the back burner because of The Summit (tm), and the concerns raised have taken a back seat to what the uber guilds put on their list.</P>
<P>Yeah, I understand that you've classified everything on our list as "wishes" instead of stuff that has any priority in your eyes.&nbsp; Continuing the billing on my accounts is dropping lower&nbsp;on my personal priority list the longer this drags on.</P>
<P>August 31 is the drop dead date.&nbsp; Anything that hasn't been addressed by then will not be addressed, because then the devs will have another major influx of expansion-specific disasters that will take priority.&nbsp; Why is it so hard for the powers that be at SOE to understand that they're running out of time?</P>
<P>Talk to us.&nbsp; Tell us when we can expect to hear a point by point response to the mega-list Brenlo collected and the top five concerns of each class.&nbsp; We're not expecting you to fix every one of them or even&nbsp;to&nbsp;promise a date&nbsp;when you'll have&nbsp;specific issues fixed.&nbsp; We're asking you to tell us which items you will fix, which you will not fix and what your rationale is for refusing to address those issues, and which are still being investigated and how we can help move that investigation along.<BR></P>	
